## ⚙️ Core Operational Pillars & Implementation Modules

### 1. Demand Management & "Use Before Buy" Controls

#### Key Execution Protocols
1. **Mandatory Storage & SLOB Cross-Checks:** Lock down the digital purchase requisition (PR) generation gateway. Bidders or departments must systematically prove that identical or substitutable components do not exist anywhere on the company's regional asset ledger or SLOB list before a PR can be authorized.
2. **Tri-Tier PR Prioritization:** Categorize all inbound non-production requirements into a strict hierarchy:
   * **Must-Have:** Direct impact on production continuity or regulatory compliance.
   * **Should-Have:** Demonstrable operational efficiency gains with < 6 months ROI.
   * **Nice-to-Have:** Discretionary spend; automatically deferred or cancelled during cost-containment cycles.
3. **Internal Surplus Marketplace:** Publish weekly excess, scrap, and unutilized material logs to enable internal departmental trading, avoiding duplicate outward sourcing.

#### Performance Metrics & Baseline Benchmarks
| Metric | Historical Baseline | Targeted Playbook Impact | Strategic Business Value |
| :--- | :---: | :---: | :--- |
| **MRO & Indirect Spend Drop** | Uncontrolled | **5% – 10% Reduction** | Directly expands EBITDA margins |
| **Spot Purchase Ratio** | 38% | **14%** | Eradicates high-premium, un-contracted buying |
| **SLOB Inventory Clearance** | High Holding | **X–Y Lakhs Liquidated/Year** | Frees up tied-up working capital |
| **PR Validation Cycle Time** | Fragmented | **10% – 15% Reduction** | Streamlines internal material planning cycles |

