### 2. Strategic Sourcing & Supplier Base Optimization

#### Key Execution Protocols
* **Annual Quantity Agreements (AQAs):** Aggregate fragmented quarterly requirements into centralized, high-volume long-term contracts. Leverage total volume leverage to extract lower unit costs while scheduling flexible, monthly/quarterly "call-off" Purchase Orders to keep warehouse footprints minimal.
* **Rigorous Multi-Quote Discipline:** Enforce an immutable policy requiring a minimum of three fully qualified, technically compliant quotes for any spend surpassing established corporate thresholds. Utilize highly structured, apples-to-apples RFQ templates to prevent hidden logistics or service surcharges.
* **Should-Cost Matrix Application:** Break down supplier quotes into basic input components:
  $$	ext{Target Cost} = 	ext{Raw Material Weight} 	imes 	ext{Index Market Rate} + 	ext{Standard Processing/Labor} + 	ext{Factory Overhead} + 	ext{Allowed Profit Margin}$$
* **Share-of-Wallet Concentration:** Reward top-tier suppliers who hit strict Quality and On-Time Delivery (OTD) metrics with expanded volumes, simultaneously lowering supplier management, tracking, and audit overheads.

#### Performance Metrics & Baseline Benchmarks
| Sourcing Indicator | Target Operational Impact | Financial / Risk Mitigation Outcome |
| :--- | :---: | :--- |
| **Contracted Unit Pricing** | **3% – 8% Absolute Reduction** | Achieved purely via volume consolidation and index tracking |
| **Procurement Admin Cost** | **10% – 20% Cost Compression** | Driven by a major reduction in manual PO revisions and invoices |
| **Supplier Proliferation** | **15% – 25% Reduction in Base** | Shrinks operational risk and streamlines supply chain tracking |
| **Spend Under Contract (%)** | **Shifted from 60% → 80%–90%** | Insulates the corporation against sudden market price volatility |

> **Real-World Portfolio Anchor:**
