### 3. Energy, Utilities & Circular Green Procurement

#### Key Execution Protocols
1. **Utility Leak Audits:** Establish monthly cross-functional maintenance and procurement walkthroughs dedicated to identifying and fixing compressed air leaks, optimizing steam traps, checking pipe insulation, and enforcing exact thermodynamic temperature controls on heavy process machinery.
2. **Closed-Loop Packaging Systems:** Collaborate with high-frequency local component suppliers to eliminate single-use cardboard boxes and wooden pallets. Transition entirely to heavy-duty plastic totes and collapsible, reusable pallets.
3. **In-Plant Segregation & Scrap Monetization:** Set up precise, source-level material separation stations (e.g., separating high-grade tool steel scrap from common mild steel turnings). This guarantees maximum raw valuation from licensed recycling brokers and prevents value dilution.
4. **Waste-to-Wealth Infrastructure:** Evaluate local regulatory and technical channels to route process by-products or combustible factory scrap directly to co-processing plants or internal boilers, simultaneously wiping out disposal costs and replacing expensive primary fuel inputs.

#### Performance Metrics & Baseline Benchmarks
| Environmental / Utility Metric | Quantifiable Target Range | Primary ESG Framework Impact |
| :--- | :---: | :--- |
| **Facility Lighting Electricity Bill** | **50% – 65% Direct Reduction** | Scope 2 Carbon Emissions Mitigation |
| **Energy Consumption per Unit Produced** | **10% – 20% Reduction** | Directly lowers the product's overall carbon footprint |
| **Energy-Related Scope 1 & 2 Emissions**| **10% – 25% Carbon Drop** | Supports global Science Based Targets initiative (SBTi) |
| **Industrial Waste Routed to Landfill** | **30% – 50% Absolute Diversion**| Drives corporate Circular Economy indexing |
| **Logistics Freight CO₂ Intensity** | **10% – 20% Drop** | Achieved via smart load building and road-to-rail mode shifts |

